org.perfcake.validation

Class RegExpValidator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.perfcake.validation.RegExpValidator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MessageValidator

    public class RegExpValidator
extends Object
implements MessageValidator

    Checks the message payload for the given regular expression.

    It is possible to set the Pattern.compile(String, int) compile flags using the particular properties.

    All flags but Pattern.UNIX_LINES are supported. That is because StringUtil.trimLines(String) is used to pre-process the message payload that changes all line breakers to \n.

    Author:
    Lucie Fabriková, Martin Večeřa, Pavel Macík
    See Also:
    Pattern.compile(String, int)
